TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Salary Differential between Male and Female Administrators: Equal Pay for Equal Work?
AU  - Sigelman, Lee
AU  - Milward, H. Brinton
AU  - Shepard, Jon M.
Y1  - 1982/09/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256088
DO  - 10.5465/256088
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 664
EP  - 671
VL  - 25
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article presents information on a study which examined the salary differential between male and female administrators in higher education institutions in the United States. The focus of research on gender-based salary differentials in public institutions of higher education is on faculty members. It reveals that female administrators were paid only about 80 percent as much as men with the same job titles who were employed by the same types of institutions in terms of salary, according to a nationwide survey of colleges and universities conducted in 1975?1976.
AB  - This article presents information on a study which examined the salary differential between male and female administrators in higher education institutions in the United States. The focus of research on gender-based salary differentials in public institutions of higher education is on faculty members. It reveals that female administrators were paid only about 80 percent as much as men with the same job titles who were employed by the same types of institutions in terms of salary, according to a nationwide survey of colleges and universities conducted in 1975?1976.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256088
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256088
Y2  - 2026/04/24
