N2  - Performance appraisals of nonmanagement employees of a large supply organization were analyzed for effects of employee and supervisor race and sex. Total race and sex effects accounted for less than 5 percent of the criterion variance. Results are compared with laboratory findings and implications for performance appraisal theory and research are discussed.
